metaData.descriptionCS: The examinee is asked to retell each story from the immediate condition. Then the examinee is asked yes/no questions about each story.

responseItems.label: Anna
responseItems.criteria: Anna or a variant of the name
responseItems.onePointResponse: Ann, Annie, Annette
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: Angela, Allison, any other name

responseItems.label: Thompson
responseItems.criteria: Thompson is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: Thompson
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: Thompkins, Thomas, any other name

responseItems.label: of South
responseItems.criteria: South (in any context)
responseItems.onePointResponse: from South, who lived in the South, who came from the South
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: any other location/direction

responseItems.label: Boston,
responseItems.criteria: Boston (in any context)
responseItems.onePointResponse: who worked in Boston, on a trip to Boston
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: any other city

responseItems.label: employed
responseItems.criteria: indication that she held a job
responseItems.onePointResponse: worked, had a job as, who earned a living as
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: employed a cook, wanted to be a cook, was a cook

responseItems.label: as a cook
responseItems.criteria: cook or some form of the word (e.g., cooked) is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: who cooked
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: as a waitress, in the kitchen

responseItems.label: in a school
responseItems.criteria: school is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: at a high school, by a school
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: in a hospital, at a company

responseItems.label: cafeteria,
responseItems.criteria: cafeteria is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: school cafeteria, lunch cafeteria
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: lunchroom, dining hall, diner, restaurant, kitchen

responseItems.label: reported
responseItems.criteria: indication that a formal statement was made to someone in authority (in any context)
responseItems.onePointResponse: filed a complaint, said to the police, made a statement, notified the police, called the police, told the police
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: said, told how

responseItems.label: at the police
responseItems.criteria: police (in any context)
responseItems.onePointResponse: police, the cops
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: any other organization

responseItems.label: station
responseItems.criteria: station (in any context) or a word or phrase denoting a police station
responseItems.onePointResponse: department, headquarters
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: office, building

responseItems.label: that she had been held up
responseItems.criteria: indication that she had been held up (e.g., gunpoint or knife)
responseItems.onePointResponse: gunpoint, knifepoint, that someone held her up, that she was in a stick-up
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: that she was beaten, she was attacked, she got mugged

responseItems.label: on State Street
responseItems.criteria: State Street (in any context)
responseItems.onePointResponse: she lived on State Street, on her way to State Street
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: State Avenue, any other street

responseItems.label: the night before
responseItems.criteria: indication that the hold-up occurred the previous night
responseItems.onePointResponse: last night, the previous night
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: at night, one night, yesterday, the day before

responseItems.label: and robbed
responseItems.criteria: indication that a robbery took place (implication that money was taken)
responseItems.onePointResponse: was robbed, her money was stolen, they took her money, someone took her purse
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: lost her money, somebody took her things

responseItems.label: of fifty-six dollars.
responseItems.criteria: indication that an amount of money greater than $49 but less than $60 was taken from her
responseItems.onePointResponse: 50-some dollars, 55 dollars, about 50 dollars
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: 65 dollars, a lot of money, the police collected her money for her

responseItems.label: She had four
responseItems.criteria: four is required, together with an indication that the children were hers
responseItems.onePointResponse: she was the mother of four, she had four kids
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: she had two, she had some, there were some

responseItems.label: small children,
responseItems.criteria: children or a synonym required
responseItems.onePointResponse: little children, kids, small kids, young children
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: babies, girls, sons, small boys, daughters

responseItems.label: the rent was due,
responseItems.criteria: indication that the rent was due
responseItems.onePointResponse: she had not paid the rent, she owed for the rent, the landlord had to be paid, she needed money for the rent
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: she owed money, she needed money, there was no money

responseItems.label: and they had not eaten
responseItems.criteria: indication that her children or the family were without food
responseItems.onePointResponse: they had gone without food, they were hungry, there was no food, her kids had nothing to eat, she couldn't feed her family
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: there wasn't much food, they had only a little food, she had not eaten, didn't have money to buy food, no reference to children not eating

responseItems.label: for two days.
responseItems.criteria: two days is required or a phrase meaning about two days (e.g., couple of days)
responseItems.onePointResponse: for a couple of days, for one or two days, for two or three days
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: for days, for several days, for a day, for three days

responseItems.label: The police,
responseItems.criteria: word or phrase signifying one or more members of the police department (in any context)
responseItems.onePointResponse: the cops, the policemen, the detectives, the police, officers, they (clearly indicating police)
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: they (unspecified), some people, her neighbors, somebody

responseItems.label: touched by the woman's story,
responseItems.criteria: indication that her story evoked sympathy
responseItems.onePointResponse: were touched, felt sorry for the woman, wanted to help her, were sympathetic
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: listened to her story, helped her, believed her

responseItems.label: took up a collection
responseItems.criteria: indication that money or a donation was collected
responseItems.onePointResponse: chipped in, collected money, donated, collected some food
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: gave her some money, found some money

responseItems.label: for her.
responseItems.criteria: indication that the money collected was for her or her children
responseItems.onePointResponse: and gave it to her, for her children, for her family, for them, to help her out
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: as a gift, to make things better

responseItems.label: At 6:00
responseItems.criteria: 6:00 is required
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: any other time

responseItems.label: on Monday
responseItems.criteria: Monday is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: Monday
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: any other day of the week

responseItems.label: evening,
responseItems.criteria: evening (in any context)
responseItems.onePointResponse: in the evening, ___ p.m. (any hour), night
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: afternoon, morning

responseItems.label: Joe
responseItems.criteria: Joe or variant of the name
responseItems.onePointResponse: Jos√©, Joseph
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: John, Jim, any other name

responseItems.label: Garcia
responseItems.criteria: Garcia is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: Garcia
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: Garza, Rodriguez, any other last name

responseItems.label: of Chicago
responseItems.criteria: Chicago is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: Chicago
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: any other city

responseItems.label: was watching television
responseItems.criteria: indication that he was watching/listening to the television
responseItems.onePointResponse: watching the news, watching a program
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: listening to the radio

responseItems.label: as he dressed
responseItems.criteria: indication that he was getting dressed
responseItems.onePointResponse: was dressing, was putting on his clothes
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: as he prepared, was getting ready

responseItems.label: to go out.
responseItems.criteria: indication that he was going out
responseItems.onePointResponse: getting ready to go
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: to go outside

responseItems.label: A weather bulletin
responseItems.criteria: indication that there was an announcement about the weather
responseItems.onePointResponse: weather report, weather forecast, weather warning, a report, an announcement
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: news report, newscast

responseItems.label: interrupted the program
responseItems.criteria: indication of a break in the regularly scheduled program
responseItems.onePointResponse: a weather report interrupted, broke into the program
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: no interruption in program mentioned

responseItems.label: to warn that thunderstorms
responseItems.criteria: indication that there was a warning about a storm
responseItems.onePointResponse: stating/advising/reporting thunderstorms/storms
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: tornado, windstorms, hailstorms, severe weather

responseItems.label: would move into the area
responseItems.criteria: indication that a storm was coming
responseItems.onePointResponse: will soon be here, on its way, heading for us, was approaching
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: storm already here, was in the area

responseItems.label: within the next two to three hours
responseItems.criteria: phrase meaning about two or three hours
responseItems.onePointResponse: in a couple of hours, two or three hours, within three hours
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: soon, in one hour, a few hours, two to six hours

responseItems.label: and remain until morning.
responseItems.criteria: indication that the storm would stay until morning
responseItems.onePointResponse: last through the night, from evening until the morning
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: continue for many hours

responseItems.label: The announcer said
responseItems.criteria: indication that someone was reporting about a storm
responseItems.onePointResponse: the announcer warned/cautioned, the reporter said
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: read in the newspaper

responseItems.label: the storm could bring hail
responseItems.criteria: indication that hail was possible
responseItems.onePointResponse: hail, considerable hail
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: snow, sleet

responseItems.label: and up to four inches
responseItems.criteria: four inches is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: approximately 4 inches
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: any other number, rain for a while

responseItems.label: of rain
responseItems.criteria: rain is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: with rain, raining
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: drizzle, snow

responseItems.label: and cause the temperature to drop
responseItems.criteria: indication that the temperature would drop or decrease (score 0 points if the examinee does not specifically mention a decrease)
responseItems.onePointResponse: temperature would fall, get colder, cool down
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: temperature would rise, get warmer

responseItems.label: by fifteen degrees.
responseItems.criteria: relative decrease of 15 degrees is required (score 1 point if the examinee mentions the correct change of 15 degrees, even if a decrease is not specified)
responseItems.onePointResponse: around 15 degrees, about 15 points
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: any number other than 15, temperature would rise 15

responseItems.label: Joe decided to stay home.
responseItems.criteria: indication that he decided to stay home
responseItems.onePointResponse: decided not to go out, decided to stay in
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: went out

responseItems.label: He took off his coat
responseItems.criteria: indication that he took off outer clothing
responseItems.onePointResponse: pulled his jacket off, removed his outer clothing
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: took his clothes off

responseItems.label: and sat down
responseItems.criteria: indication that he sat down
responseItems.onePointResponse: sat down to watch
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: went to bed, he lay down

responseItems.label: to watch old movies.
responseItems.criteria: indication of viewing movies is required
responseItems.onePointResponse: old movies on television
responseItems.zeroPointResponse: watch television

items.question: Was the woman's name Diana Thompson?
Was the story set in South Boston?
Was the woman a cook?
Did she work in a restaurant?
Did she have four children?
Were the children teenagers?
Did the robbery take place on Sixth Street?
Did the woman report being robbed two nights before?
Did she report the robbery at the police station?
Was the woman robbed of seventy-five dollars?
Did the family go without food for four days?
Was the rent due?
Did the police catch the thief?
Did the police feel sorry for the woman?
Did the police take up a collection?
Was the man's name Joe Garcia?
Was it Sunday evening?
Was it 6:00?
Was the story set in Seattle?
Was the man dressing to go out?
Was he watching television?
Was the program interrupted?
Was the storm expected to move into the area on Tuesday?
Was the storm expected to stay in the area through the night?
Was the temperature expected to drop 30 degrees?
Did the announcer predict 10 inches of rain?
Did the announcer warn of possible flooding?
Did the announcer warn that it could hail?
Did the man decide to stay home?
Did he sit down to watch a sports program?
